.TH PATHCHK "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pathchk \- check whether file names are valid or portable
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pathchk
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... \fI\,NAME\/\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Diagnose invalid or non\-portable file names.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#pathchk-p'\fB\-p\fP\X'tty: link'
check for most POSIX systems
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#pathchk-P'\fB\-P\fP\X'tty: link'
check for empty names and leading "\-"
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#pathchk--portability'\fB\-\-portability\fP\X'tty: link'
check for all POSIX systems (equivalent to \fB\-p\fR \fB\-P\fR)
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/pathchk#pathchk--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/pathchk#pathchk--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
